condition.narrative: The Recipient shall not later than 6 months from the Effectiveness Date establish, within MoFEP, a Project Inter-MinisterialCommittee (PIOC), chaired by MoFEP and co-chaired by MoLSD, with a composition, mandate and resources satisfactory to the Bank, tobe responsible for, among others, providing policy and strategic guidance and direction on Project implementation and reviewingprogress towards achievement of Project objectives and advising on any issues thereof.

The Recipient shall not later than nine (9) months from the Effectiveness Date of the Original Project, establish and thereaftermaintain throughout Project implementation, the Digital Economy Agency (DEA) under Minister of MoFEP, with a composition, mandateand resources satisfactory to the Association.

The Recipient shall not later than nine (9) months from the Effectiveness Date, establish and thereafter maintain throughoutProject implementation, the Digital Economy Agency (DEA), with a composition, mandate and resources satisfactory to the Bank;

actual.value: The project began initial activities to support outreach and registration, enrollment, beneficiary verification, payment delivery,GRM, monitoring, and capacity building. It will also establish operational procedures, an SFSP Management Information System (MIS),necessary expansion and enhancements to the National Civil Registry (NCR), and an enabling legal framework for data protection andprivacy. The project supports both the delivery cycle (registration, enrollment, payment, and GRM) as well as supporting systems.All these systems are nascent and will require continuous strengthening.
